==Arabic==
===Etymology===
From the verb {{ARchar|[[كعب]]}} (káʕaba), to be full and round; {{ARchar|[[كعب]]}} (káʕʕaba), to make cubic.

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|كعبة}}''' (káʕba) {{f}}, {{ARchar|[[كعبات]]}} (kaʕabāt) {{p}}

# [[cube]], a cubic structure
#''(figurative)'' [[shrine]], [[focus]] of interest
# [[virginity]]

